{"word":"κοιλία","slug":"κοιλία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰοιλία, ας, ἡ</el></b> [<el>ϰοῖλος</el> ‘body cavity’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> belly, stomach <a href='B:470 12:40'>Mt 12:40</a>; <a href='B:470 15:17'>15:17</a>; <a href='B:490 15:16'>Lk 15:16</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:520 16:18'>Ro 16:18</a>; <a href='B:530 6:13'>1 Cor 6:13</a>; <a href='B:570 3:19'>Phil 3:19</a>; <a href='B:730 10:9'>Rv 10:9f</a>.</b> In imagery as expression of the inner life <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐκ\">ἐκ</a> τῆς ϰοιλίας <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:αὐτοῦ\">αὐτοῦ</a></el>, which = in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Engl.\">Engl.</a> a circumlocution such as from deep within him <b><a href='B:500 7:38'>J 7:38</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp> womb <a href='B:490 1:41'>Lk 1:41f</a>, 44; <a href='B:490 2:21'>2:21</a>; <a href='B:490 11:27'>11:27</a>; <a href='B:490 23:29'>23:29</a>; <a href='B:500 3:4'>J 3:4</a>.</b> Idiom: <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐκ\">ἐκ</a> ϰοιλίας μητρὸς</el> = from birth <b><a href='B:470 19:12'>Mt 19:12</a>; <a href='B:490 1:15'>Lk 1:15</a>; <a href='B:510 3:2'>Ac 3:2</a>; <a href='B:510 14:8'>14:8</a>; <a href='B:550 1:15'>Gal 1:15</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:κοδράντης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:κοιμάω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}